definition:
A man of the Cushites living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.10.7; 
 son of: Cush (H3568); 
 brother of: Seba (H5434), Havilah (H2341H), Sabtah (H5454), Sabteca (H5455) and Nimrod (H5248); 
 father of: Sheba (H7614) and Dedan (H1719B); also called Raama at 1Ch.1.9;  Raama at 1Ch.1.9; 
 § Raamah = "horse's mane"
1) son of Cush and father of Sheba and Dedan
2) a home of traders
